Captain Alastair Cook scored 130 as England set India a target of 310 runs off 49 overs to win the first Test in Rajkot on Sunday.The tourists declared on 260 for 3 whenh Cook was out shortly after lunch on the final day at the Saurashtra Cricket Association ground in Rajkot.Brief scores:England: 537 and 260-3 dec (75.3 overs, Cook 130, Hameed 82). India: 488-AFP